BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Santa Rosa Junior College
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260421T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260421T170000
LOCATION:Bertolini Student Activity Center - Santa Rosa Campus
SUMMARY:Free Training on Trauma-Informed Care and Workplace Wellbeing
DESCRIPTION:We are excited to share that the Social Work and Human Servic
 es program is hosting a free training on Trauma-Informed Care and Workpla
 ce Wellbeing\, presented by Hanna Center\, for our SWHS students and the 
 broader campus community!  Date: April 21st\, 2026  Time: 3:00–5:00 PM 
  Location: SRJC Student Activity Center (SAC)  This 2-hour interactive se
 ssion will explore the principles of Trauma-Informed Care and their appli
 cation in professional environments. Participants will learn how to recog
 nize and respond to signs of burnout\, compassion fatigue\, and vicarious
  trauma — and develop strategies to strengthen resilience and wellbeing
 .  This training is especially valuable for anyone in the helping profess
 ions or those looking to foster a more supportive\, trauma-informed workp
 lace culture.  For more support\, visit SRJC's Human Services website. (h
 ttps://humanservices.santarosa.edu/)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  We are excited to share that the Social
  Work and Human Services program is hosting a free training on Trauma-Inf
 ormed Care and Workplace Wellbeing\, presented by Hanna Center\, for our 
 SWHS students and the broader campus community!</p><p>  Date: April 21st\
 , 2026<br />  Time: 3:00–5:00 PM<br />  Location: SRJC Student Activity
  Center (SAC)</p><p>  This 2-hour interactive session will explore the pr
 inciples of Trauma-Informed Care and their application in professional en
 vironments. Participants will learn how to recognize and respond to signs
  of burnout\, compassion fatigue\, and vicarious trauma — and develop s
 trategies to strengthen resilience and wellbeing.</p><p>  This training i
 s especially valuable for anyone in the helping professions or those look
 ing to foster a more supportive\, trauma-informed workplace culture.</p><
 p>  For more support\, <a href="https://humanservices.santarosa.edu/" tar
 get="_blank" rel="noopener">visit SRJC's Human Services website.</a></p>
UID:20260421T220000Z-17033@calendar.santarosa.edu
