SUMMARY:The Calder Quartet - SRJC's Chamber Concert Series
DESCRIPTION:Hailed as "superb" and "imaginative\, skillful creators" by t
 he New York Times\, the Calder Quartet captivates audiences\, exploring a
  broad spectrum of repertoire\, always striving to fulfill the composer's
  vision in its performances. The group's distinctive artistry is exemplif
 ied by a musical curiosity brought to everything they perform and has led
  them to be called "one of America's most satisfying–and most enterpris
 ing–quartets."  Winners of the prestigious 2014 Avery Fisher Career Gra
 nt\, they are widely known for the discovery\, commissioning\, recording 
 and mentoring of some of today's best emerging composers.  Benjamin Jacob
 son\, violin\; Tereza Stanislav\, violin\; Jonathan Moerschel\, viola\; a
 nd Eric Byers\, cello  &#160\;  Program:  Philip Glass\, String Quartet N
 o. 2\, "Company"  Ben Johnston\, String Quartet No. 4\, "Amazing Grace"  
 Samuel Barber\, String Quartet in B minor Op. 11  Andrew Norman\, Sabrina
  (arr. for string quartet)  Florence Price\, String Quartet No. 2*Recepti
 on immediately following concert  &#160\;  Ticket Prices:  Season tickets
  (all 6 concerts): $155  Mini Season (any 3 concerts): $90  Individual ti
 ckets: $35  Student tickets (with valid ID): $20  &#160\;Buy tickets here
 ! (https://www.cityboxoffice.com/?category=36)  SRJC Chamber Concerts Web
 site: https://chamberconcerts.santarosa.edu/ (https://chamberconcerts.san
 tarosa.edu/)&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Hailed as "superb" and "imaginative\, s
 killful creators" by the New York Times\, the Calder Quartet captivates a
 udiences\, exploring a broad spectrum of repertoire\, always striving to 
 fulfill the composer's vision in its performances. The group's distinctiv
 e artistry is exemplified by a musical curiosity brought to everything th
 ey perform and has led them to be called "one of America's most satisfyin
 g–and most enterprising–quartets."<br />  Winners of the prestigious 
 2014 Avery Fisher Career Grant\, they are widely known for the discovery\
 , commissioning\, recording and mentoring of some of today's best emergin
 g composers.</p><p>  Benjamin Jacobson\, violin\; Tereza Stanislav\, viol
 in\; Jonathan Moerschel\, viola\; and Eric Byers\, cello</p><p>  &#160\;<
 /p><p>  Program:<br />  Philip Glass\, String Quartet No. 2\, "Company"<b
 r />  Ben Johnston\, String Quartet No. 4\, "Amazing Grace"<br />  Samuel
  Barber\, String Quartet in B minor Op. 11<br />  Andrew Norman\, Sabrina
  (arr. for string quartet)<br />  Florence Price\, String Quartet No. 2</
 p><p><em>*Reception immediately following concert</em></p><p>  &#160\;</p
 ><p>  Ticket Prices:<br />  Season tickets (all 6 concerts): $155<br />  
 Mini Season (any 3 concerts): $90<br />  Individual tickets: $35<br />  S
 tudent tickets (with valid ID): $20</p><p>  &#160\;</p><p><a href="https:
 //www.cityboxoffice.com/?category=36" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy 
 tickets here!</a></p><p>  SRJC Chamber Concerts Website: <a href="https:/
 /chamberconcerts.santarosa.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://c
 hamberconcerts.santarosa.edu/</a>&#160\;</p>
