LOCATION:Intercultural Center\, Pioneer Hall\, Room 380 - Santa Rosa Campus
SUMMARY:Disabled & Queer Joy Night
DESCRIPTION:Join the SRJC Disability Cultural Center (DCC) and Queer Reso
 urce Center (QRC) for an afternoon of connection\, creativity\, and commu
 nity! Disabled &amp\; Queer Joy Night is a low-pressure mixer designed fo
 r disabled and queer folks (and those who live at the intersection of bot
 h) to come together\, relax\, and celebrate joy in all its forms.  Come h
 ang out\, meet new people\, and enjoy:Snacks and refreshments  Chill craf
 ts and creative activities  Games and casual fun  A welcoming\, affirming
  space to just be    Whether you're looking to make new friends\, connect
  with community\, or simply unwind in a space that celebrates you—you b
 elong here.  April 29th  3:00–5:00 PM  SRJC Intercultural Center\, Pion
 eer Hall\, Room 380  This event is open to students\, staff\, community m
 embers\, and anyone in between. Bring yourself\, bring a friend\, or come
  solo—there's space for you here.  For more information\, visit the DCC
  website here! (https://drd.santarosa.edu/dcc)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Join the SRJC Disability Cultural Cente
 r (DCC) and Queer Resource Center (QRC) for an afternoon of connection\, 
 creativity\, and community! Disabled &amp\; Queer Joy Night is a low-pres
 sure mixer designed for disabled and queer folks (and those who live at t
 he intersection of both) to come together\, relax\, and celebrate joy in 
 all its forms.</p><p>  Come hang out\, meet new people\, and enjoy:</p><u
 l><li>Snacks and refreshments  </li><li>Chill crafts and creative activit
 ies  </li><li>Games and casual fun  </li><li>A welcoming\, affirming spac
 e to just be  </li></ul><p>  Whether you're looking to make new friends\,
  connect with community\, or simply unwind in a space that celebrates you
 —you belong here.</p><p>  April 29th<br />  3:00–5:00 PM<br />  SRJC 
 Intercultural Center\, Pioneer Hall\, Room 380</p><p>  This event is open
  to students\, staff\, community members\, and anyone in between. Bring y
 ourself\, bring a friend\, or come solo—there's space for you here.</p>
 <p>  For more information\, <a href="https://drd.santarosa.edu/dcc" targe
 t="_blank" rel="noopener">visit the DCC website here!</a></p>
