SUMMARY:Lessons From The Dream Movement
DESCRIPTION:Using the past\, to inform the present\, to shape the future.
   From Dream Clubs in local colleges to a national movement\, undocumente
 d youth turned isolation into community and community into power. Whether
  you're into history\, social movements\, or you're simply curious about 
 how a disenfranchised community built national influence\, this conversat
 ion is for you!Register here! (https://events.zoom.us/ev/Ari35dd7sJIXd1xy
 PWqFl8TB6Y-YQK7kmCwVt4RVvIF1H-qxG3hS~AnvT0N5dg7dUYGAFFZGL1RJZwCmuHCNaOQ_h
 A4u2EActwtE3JnWx7OxGXg)  For more information\, visit the SRJC Undocu •
  Immigrant • Dream Center Website (https://dream.santarosa.edu/workshop
 s-events-2025-2026)
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Using the past\, to inform the present\
 , to shape the future.</p><p>  From Dream Clubs in local colleges to a na
 tional movement\, undocumented youth turned isolation into community and 
 community into power. Whether you're into history\, social movements\, or
  you're simply curious about how a disenfranchised community built nation
 al influence\, this conversation is for you!</p><p><a href="https://event
 s.zoom.us/ev/Ari35dd7sJIXd1xyPWqFl8TB6Y-YQK7kmCwVt4RVvIF1H-qxG3hS~AnvT0N5
